    "body": "Alternative clients, nor mainline clients, have -never- had to release a dummy update, due to the current release scheme.  That's a red herring, and an invalid justification.  The network protocol has always been backwards compatible, even way back to ancient client versions.\n\nI understand the desire to separate the two versions, but beyond that point you're making up nonsensical justifications for problems that don't exist.\n",
