    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I would like to see this issue addressed. As someone starting another Bitcoin client it concerns me greatly that the core Bitcoin client is trying to monopolise what should be decentralised currency. How are we supposed to differentiate between protocol version and client? A client shouldn't be the protocol and forcing it to be the same thing is a silly coupling.\n\nblueCommand also makes a good point for the health of the network. Knowing the client composition is important.\n",
